# The Issue Tracker Is a Plan Artifact (writes allowed in Plan mode)

The issue-tracker plugin (`.cursor/plugins/issue-tracker`) is this project's
canonical store for plans. A Project > Epic > Branch > Commit tree in the
tracker **is** the plan — the equivalent of a written plan document. Its
`issues/<id>/issue.json` and `description.md` files are plan artifacts, not
source code or system state.

Therefore, in **Plan mode**, using the issue-tracker CLI to create or update
that plan is explicitly permitted and encouraged — it is the same kind of write
as calling the plan tool or editing a plan markdown file. This includes:
`apply <file>`, `create-project`, `create-epic`, `add-branch`, `add-commit`,
`<kind> get|set` (e.g. `<kind> set <id> description --file <path>`,
`<kind> set <id> partOf <parent>`, `epic set <id> blockedBy --add <epicId>`,
`<kind> set <id> assignee <who>`), `comment`, `delete`.

Still NOT allowed in Plan mode (unchanged): editing source code, running builds
or tests, git writes, or any other system-mutating command. The carve-out is
scoped strictly to authoring plans in the issue-tracker.
